<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Using a micrometer (2), measure the thickness of the removed shim (1), and determine replacement shim by calculating the thickness of new shim with the following formula and table.
</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>
Shim thickness specification
</title>
<ptxt>
Intake side:
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
A = B + C – 0.20 mm (0.008 in.)
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Exhaust side:
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
A = B + C – 0.30 mm (0.012 in.)
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
A: Thickness of new shim
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
B: Thickness of removed shim
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
C: Measured valve clearance
</ptxt>
</spec>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I2RH0B140014.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "51.000mm" ver = "01" gw = "193" gh = "128"/>
</figure>
<ptxt>
<emph etype = "bold">
Example of intake side:
</emph>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
When thickness of removed shim is 2.40 mm (0.094 in.), and measured valve clearance is 0.45 mm (0.018 in.).
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
A = 2.40 mm (0.094 in.) + 0.45 mm (0.018 in.) – 0.20 mm (0.008 in.) = 2.65 mm (0.104 in.) 
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Calculated thickness of new shim = 2.65 mm (0.104 in.)
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Select new shim No. (1) with a thickness as close as possible to calculated value.
</ptxt>
